    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Pete Crow-Armstrong** serving as our clear offensive anchor. Facing V\u00e1squez, R with a favorable 5.43 xERA, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** nets a 74.86 score; while his #9 spot in the order acts as a drag, the significant SP skill advantage and a dynamic platoon edge make him our highest-ceiling producer. **Hyeseong Kim** also earns a strong recommendation (63.95) against Chris Paddack, benefiting from a high SP xERA and a helpful wind direction that should assist his power profile, despite the relative lineup suppression of hitting eighth.\n\nConversely, our bench decisions were highlighted by the difficult exclusion of candidates who couldn't overcome the current day\u2019s unfavorable environmental factors. **Chase Meidroth** (48.71) barely scraped into the active roster and remains our riskiest play; a 38% rain risk and an unfavorable wind blowing inward significantly throttled his efficiency, nearly pushing him to the bench in favor of safer defensive depth. While we are missing the offensive production of **Yordan Alvarez**, **Trea Turner**, and **Kyle Schwarber** due to today's schedule, and waiting on **Christian Yelich**\u2019s return from the IL, we are focused on leveraging the speed of **Caleb Durbin** (46.23). Although **Caleb Durbin** faces a tough arm in Cease, his elite ability to hunt stolen bases against a pitcher with a slow delivery provides an intangible boost that keeps him in the mix even when the raw projections are marginal. **Kazuma Okamoto** and **Junior Caminero** round out the active core, with both players offering stable, if unspectacular, floors against their respective left-handed matchups.",
